  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "WHO releases Monkeypox report",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Health Organization (WHO) has stopped raising the apex warning to a higher level during an emergency committee meeting.",
        "However, the head of the United Nations Observatory for Human Rights, Tedros Gabrias, described it as an \"evolving health threat.\"",
        "\"I am deeply concerned about the spread of monkeypox, which has now been identified in more than 50 countries across five WHO regions with 3,000 patients since early May,\" the chief said in a statement after the meeting.",
        "The International Health Regulations Emergency Committee, comprising of health experts and scientists from around the world, noted that \"many aspects of the current epidemic are unusual.\"",
        "However, \"despite several members expressing different views,\" the committee finally came to an agreement and advised that \"in this case, the departure of this spring should not be considered a state of emergency.\""
      ],
